# **Bitcoin Analysis using Plotly and Forecasting with LSTM and Kraken API**

## **Overview**

This project forecasts Bitcoin (BTC) prices using historical and real-time data fetched from the Kraken API and builds an LSTM-based deep learning model for time-series forecasting. The project includes data fetching, preprocessing, visualization using Plotly, and predictive modeling using TensorFlow's LSTM network.

All visualizations (SMA, Volatility Bands, Percent Change, and Forecast Plot) are built with Plotly and are interactive. The project is containerized with Docker for ease of deployment.

**Features**

* Fetches historical BTC/USD prices (past 10,000 minutes)  
* Streams real-time BTC price from Kraken  
* Computes SMA, Volatility Bands, Percent Change  
* Trains LSTM model for next 60-minute forecast  
* Visualizes all key insights using Plotly  
* Dockerized pipeline for scalable deployment

**Dependencies**

Install from `requirements.txt`:

```
pandas
numpy
requests
scikit-learn
tensorflow
plotly
```

**Project Structure**

```
btc-forecast/
├── btc_forecast.py         # Main forecasting and visualization script
├── Dockerfile              # Docker build instructions
├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies
├── DATA605 - Project Report.pdf
└── README.md               # This file
```

**Running the Project**

### **Without Docker**

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
python btc_forecast.py
```

### **With Docker**

```
docker build -t btc-forecast .
docker run --rm btc-forecast
```

**Flowchart** 

```
graph TD
    A[Start: btc_forecast.py] --> B[Fetch Historical BTC Prices\n(Kraken OHLC API)]
    B --> C[Fetch Real-Time BTC Price\n(Kraken Ticker API)]
    C --> D[Combine Historical + Live Data\nAlign timestamps, drop nulls]
    D --> E[Perform Analytics:\nSMA, Volatility, Percent Change]
    E --> F[Plot Interactive Graphs\n(Plotly: Price, Volatility, % Change)]
    F --> G[Prepare LSTM Sequences\n60-min input, 60-min output]
    G --> H[Train LSTM Model\n5 epochs, batch size 64]
    H --> I[Forecast Next 60 Minutes]
    I --> J[Evaluate Model\nMAE, MSE]
    J --> K[Plot Forecast vs Actual\n(Plotly)]
```
